-- Sarkozy’s Party Seeks No Le Pen Alliance, Baroin Tells Figaro
-- B y   F a b i o   B e n e d e t t i - V a l e n t i n i
-- 2012-04-28T09:46:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-28/sarkozy-s-party-seeks-no-le-pen-alliance-baroin-tells-figaro.html
French President  Nicolas Sarkozy ’s
party, the Union pour un Mouvement Populaire, or UMP, isn’t
seeking an alliance with the anti-euro Front National, led by
Marine Le Pen, Finance Minister  Francois Baroin  told  Le Figaro 
in an interview.  Le Pen took third place in the first round of elections on
April 22, winning 17.9 percent. Sarkozy took 27.2 percent,
trailing Socialist Francois Hollande, who took 28.6 percent.
Hollande and Sarkozy go to the polls in a May 6 run-off.  To contact the reporter on this story:
